{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"2812","heading":"Lease-purchase of facilities","label":"2812 Lease-purchase of facilities","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/stA/ptIV/ch169/schI","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs2812","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","Amendments2017—Subsec. (c)(1). added par. (1) and struck out former par. (1) which set out justification, economic analysis, and wait requirements for entering into a lease.Pub. L. 115–912003—Subsec. (c)(1)(B). inserted before period at end “or, if over sooner, a period of 14 days has expired following the date on which a copy of the justification and economic analysis are provided in an electronic medium pursuant to ”.Pub. L. 108–136section 480 of this title1990—Subsec. (a)(2)(I). added subpar. (I).Pub. L. 101–510"],"amendments":["Amendments2017—Subsec. (c)(1). added par. (1) and struck out former par. (1) which set out justification, economic analysis, and wait requirements for entering into a lease.Pub. L. 115–912003—Subsec. (c)(1)(B). inserted before period at end “or, if over sooner, a period of 14 days has expired following the date on which a copy of the justification and economic analysis are provided in an electronic medium pursuant to ”.Pub. L. 108–136section 480 of this title1990—Subsec. (a)(2)(I). added subpar. (I).Pub. L. 101–510"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":null,"label":"a","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs2812%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs2812%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary concerned may enter into an agreement with a private contractor for the lease of a facility of the kind specified in paragraph (2) if the facility is provided at the expense of the contractor on a military installation under the jurisdiction of the Department of Defense.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs2812%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/a/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs2812%2Fa%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Administrative office facilities.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/a/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs2812%2Fa%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Troop housing facilities.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/a/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs2812%2Fa%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Energy production facilities.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/a/2/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs2812%2Fa%2F2%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Utilities, including potable and waste water treatment facilities.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"E","heading":null,"label":"E","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/a/2/E","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs2812%2Fa%2F2%2FE","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Hospital and medical facilities.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"F","heading":null,"label":"F","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/a/2/F","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs2812%2Fa%2F2%2FF","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Transient quarters.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"G","heading":null,"label":"G","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/a/2/G","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs2812%2Fa%2F2%2FG","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Depot or storage facilities.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"H","heading":null,"label":"H","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/a/2/H","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs2812%2Fa%2F2%2FH","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Child care centers.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"I","heading":null,"label":"I","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/a/2/I","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs2812%2Fa%2F2%2FI","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Classroom and laboratories.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":null,"label":"b","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs2812%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs2812%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"may not exceed a term of 32 years;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs2812%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"shall provide that, at the end of the term of the lease, title to the leased facility shall vest in the United States; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs2812%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"shall include such other terms and conditions as the Secretary concerned determines are necessary or desirable to protect the interests of the United States.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":null,"label":"c","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs2812%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs2812%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary concerned may enter into a lease under this section only after the end of the 14-day period beginning on the date on which the Secretary submits, in an electronic medium pursuant to , to the appropriate committees of Congress a justification of the need for the facility covered by the proposed lease, including an economic analysis (based upon accepted life-cycle costing procedures) that demonstrates the cost effectiveness of the proposed lease compared with a military construction project for the same facility.section 480 of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs2812%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/c/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs2812%2Fc%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"not more than three leases in fiscal year 1990; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/c/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs2812%2Fc%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"not more than five leases in each of the fiscal years 1991 and 1992.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":null,"label":"d","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2812","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs2812%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Each lease entered into under this section shall include a provision that the obligation of the United States to make payments under the lease in any fiscal year is subject to the availability of appropriations for that purpose.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
